    "schema_version": "Tier 1 v1.2",
    "kingdom_note": "First cyanobacterium in canonical roster. Arthrospira platensis (commercial trade name 'Spirulina'). Note: the scientific genus Spirulina is taxonomically distinct from Arthrospira — commercial 'spirulina' products are Arthrospira platensis or A. maxima.",
    "structural_finding": "Spirulina exhibits 'commercial loanword' globalization: nearly every country has just 'Spirulina' + a local descriptive (e.g. Blue-green algae, Spiruline, Espirulina, 螺旋藻). Zero pharmacopoeia, zero traditional. Contrasts sharply with Reishi's six-layer multiplexity.",
    "low_to_medium_cap_rationale": "Gus override for this plant only: Spirulina batch leaned heavily on 'low' confidence (~40 entries). Capping aligns with Reishi/chamomile's 2-level visibility (high/medium). Do not apply this rule to future plants without explicit decision.",
    "compound_reclassification_rationale": "'Spirulina alga' / 'Alga spirulina' / 'Spirulina algae' / 'Spirulina yosunu' / 'Spirulina riasa' / 'Spirulina-Alge' / 'Ganggang spirulina' etc. are product-shelf descriptors (commercial), not linguistic-folk vocabulary."
